{"title_page": "Melipeuco", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See the Table at Infobox Settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage-->\n|official_name          = Melipueco\n|other_name             =\n|native_name            =  <!-- for cities whose native name is not in English -->\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = [[List of towns in Chile|Town]] and [[Communes of Chile|Commune]]\n|motto                  =\n|image_skyline          = \n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = \n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              =\n| flag_alt                = Flag\n|image_shield           = \n|shield_size            =\n| shield_alt              = Coat of arms\n|image_map              = Comuna de Melipeuco.svg\n|map_caption            = Map of Melipeuco commune in the Araucania Region\n|map_alt            = Map of Melipeuco commune in the Araucania Region\n|pushpin_map            = Chile\n|pushpin_label_position = bottom\n|pushpin_map_caption    = Location in Chile\n| pushpin_map_narrow     = 1\n|coor_pinpoint          = city\n|coordinates_footnotes  = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|38|51|S|71|42|W|region:CL-AR|display=inline,title}}\n|subdivision_type       = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name       = [[Chile]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Regions of Chile|Region]]\n|subdivision_name1      = [[Araucan\u00eda Region|Araucan\u00eda]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Provinces of Chile|Province]]\n|subdivision_name2      = [[Caut\u00edn Province|Caut\u00edn]]\n| government_footnotes = <ref name=\"Munitel\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.munitel.cl/ |title=Asociaci\u00f3n Chilena de Municipalidades |accessdate=23 February 2011 |language=es |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110419202659/http://www.munitel.cl/ |archivedate=19 April 2011 }}</ref><ref name=\"Official\">{{Cite web |url = http://www.melipeuco.cl/ |title = Municipality of Melipeuco |accessdate = 23 February 2011 |language = es |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170915001335/http://melipeuco.cl/ |archive-date = 15 September 2017 |url-status = dead }}</ref>\n| government_type         = [[Municipality]]\n| leader_title            = [[Alcalde]]\n| leader_party = [[Independent Democratic Union|UDI]]\n| leader_name = Eduardo Navarrete Fuentes\n|established_title      =  \n|established_date       = \n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_footnotes          = <ref name=\"INE\">{{Cite web |url= http://www.ine.cl/canales/chile_estadistico/censos_poblacion_vivienda/censo_pobl_vivi.php |title= National Statistics Institute |accessdate=13 December 2010|language=es}}</ref>\n| area_total_km2          = 1107.3\n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = 461\n| population_footnotes    = <ref name=\"INE\"/>\n| population_total        = 5590\n| population_as_of        = 2012 Census\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      = \n| population_blank1_title = [[Urban area|Urban]]\n| population_blank1       = 2333\n| population_blank2_title = [[Rural area|Rural]]\n| population_blank2       = 3295\n| demographics_type1      = Sex\n| demographics1_footnotes = <ref name=\"INE\"/> \n| demographics1_title1    = Men\n| demographics1_info1     = 2,906\n| demographics1_title2    = Women\n| demographics1_info2     = 2,722\n| timezone = [[Time in Chile|CLT]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.world-time-zones.org/zones/chile-time.htm |accessdate=2010-07-29 |title=Chile Time |publisher=WorldTimeZones.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070911130719/http://www.world-time-zones.org/zones/chile-time.htm |archivedate=2007-09-11 }}</ref>\n| utc_offset = -4\n| timezone_DST = [[Time in Chile|CLST]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.world-time-zones.org/zones/chile-summer-time.htm |accessdate=2010-07-29 |title=Chile Summer Time |publisher=WorldTimeZones.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070911130451/http://www.world-time-zones.org/zones/chile-summer-time.htm |archivedate=2007-09-11 }}</ref>\n| utc_offset_DST = -3\n|postal_code_type       =  \n|postal_code            =\n|area_code              = ''country'' 56 + ''city'' 45\n|website                = {{URL|http://www.melipeuco.cl}}\n|footnotes              = \n}} \n'''Melipeuco''' ({{IPA-es|meli\u02c8pewko}}) is a [[List of towns in Chile|town]] and [[Communes of Chile|commune]] ({{lang-es|comuna}}) in [[Chile]], located at the foot of the [[Andes]], in the [[Caut\u00edn Province|Province of Caut\u00edn]], [[Araucan\u00eda Region]]. Melipeuco is {{convert|12|km|0|abbr=on}} from the southern entrance of the [[Conguill\u00edo National Park]]. The [[Nevados de Sollipulli]], an ice-filled volcanic [[caldera]] surrounded by numerous hot water springs and geysers, lie south of the town. Lake Carilafqu\u00e9n is also located in this area. At the edge of the Nevados de Sollipulli, at the Alpehue intersection {{convert|33|km|0|abbr=on}} away, there are several hot springs with water from {{convert|40|to|70|C|F}}, even in the middle of glacier blocks.\n\n==Demographics==\nAccording to the 2002 [[census]] of the [[National Statistics Institute (Chile)|National Statistics Institute]], Melipeuco spans an area of {{convert|1107.3|sqkm|0|abbr=on}} and has 5,628 inhabitants (2,906 men and 2,722 women). Of these, 2,333 (41.5%) lived in [[urban area]]s and 3,295 (58.5%) in [[rural area]]s. The population grew by 5.9% (315 persons) between the 1992 and 2002 censuses.<ref name= \"INE\"/>\n\n==Administration==\nAs a commune, Melipeuco is a third-level [[administrative division of Chile]] administered by a [[municipal council]], headed by an [[alcalde]] who is directly elected every four years. The 2008-2012 alcalde is Eduardo Navarrete Fuentes ([[Independent Democratic Union|UDI]]).<ref name=\"Munitel\"/><ref name=\"Official\"/>\n\nWithin the [[electoral divisions of Chile]], Melipeuco is represented in the [[Chamber of Deputies of Chile|Chamber of Deputies]] by Enrique Estay (UDI) and Fuad Chah\u00edn ([[Christian Democratic Party|PDC]]) as part of the 49th electoral district, (together with [[Victoria, Chile|Victoria]], [[Curacaut\u00edn]], [[Lonquimay]], [[Vilc\u00fan]], [[Lautaro, Chile|Lautaro]], [[Perquenco]] and [[Galvarino, Chile|Galvarino]]). The commune is represented in the [[Senate of Chile|Senate]] by Alberto Espina Otero ([[National Renewal (Chile)|RN]]) and Jaime Quintana Leal ([[Party for Democracy (Chile)|PPD]]) as part of the 14th senatorial constituency (Araucan\u00eda-North).\n\n==View==\n[[File:Iss038e012569, Caldera Sollipulli.jpg|500px|left|thumb|<center>''Sollipulli''</center>]]\n{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{in lang|es}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20170915001335/http://melipeuco.cl/ Municipality of Melipeuco]\n\n{{Communes in Araucan\u00eda Region}}\n\n[[Category:Communes of Chile]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1981]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Caut\u00edn Province]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See the Table at Infobox Settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage-->\n|official_name          = Melipueco\n|other_name             =\n|native_name            =  <!-- for cities whose native name is not in English -->\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = [[List of towns in Chile|Town]] and [[Communes of Chile|Commune]]\n|motto                  =\n|image_skyline          = \n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = \n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              =\n| flag_alt                = Flag\n|image_shield           = \n|shield_size            =\n| shield_alt              = Coat of arms\n|image_map              = Comuna de Melipeuco.svg\n|map_caption            = Map of Melipeuco commune in the Araucania Region\n|map_alt            = Map of Melipeuco commune in the Araucania Region\n|pushpin_map            = Chile\n|pushpin_label_position = bottom\n|pushpin_map_caption    = Location in Chile\n| pushpin_map_narrow     = 1\n|coor_pinpoint          = city\n|coordinates_footnotes  = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|38|51|S|71|42|W|region:CL-AR|display=inline,title}}\n|subdivision_type       = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name       = [[Chile]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Regions of Chile|Region]]\n|subdivision_name1      = [[Araucan\u00eda Region|Araucan\u00eda]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Provinces of Chile|Province]]\n|subdivision_name2      = [[Caut\u00edn Province|Caut\u00edn]]\n| government_footnotes = <ref name=\"Munitel\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.munitel.cl/ |title=Asociaci\u00f3n Chilena de Municipalidades |accessdate=23 February 2011 |language=es |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110419202659/http://www.munitel.cl/ |archivedate=19 April 2011 }}</ref><ref name=\"Official\">{{Cite web |url = http://www.melipeuco.cl/ |title = Municipality of Melipeuco |accessdate = 23 February 2011 |language = es |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170915001335/http://melipeuco.cl/ |archive-date = 15 September 2017 |url-status = dead }}</ref>\n| government_type         = [[Municipality]]\n| leader_title            = [[Alcalde]]\n| leader_party = [[Independent Democratic Union|UDI]]\n| leader_name = Eduardo Navarrete Fuentes\n|established_title      =  \n|established_date       = \n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_footnotes          = <ref name=\"INE\">{{Cite web |url= http://www.ine.cl/canales/chile_estadistico/censos_poblacion_vivienda/censo_pobl_vivi.php |title= National Statistics Institute |accessdate=13 December 2010|language=es}}</ref>\n| area_total_km2          = 1107.3\n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = 461\n| population_footnotes    = <ref name=\"INE\"/>\n| population_total        = 5590\n| population_as_of        = 2012 Census\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      = \n| population_blank1_title = [[Urban area|Urban]]\n| population_blank1       = 2333\n| population_blank2_title = [[Rural area|Rural]]\n| population_blank2       = 3295\n| demographics_type1      = Sex\n| demographics1_footnotes = <ref name=\"INE\"/> \n| demographics1_title1    = Men\n| demographics1_info1     = 2,906\n| demographics1_title2    = Women\n| demographics1_info2     = 2,722\n| timezone = [[Time in Chile|CLT]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.world-time-zones.org/zones/chile-time.htm |accessdate=2010-07-29 |title=Chile Time |publisher=WorldTimeZones.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070911130719/http://www.world-time-zones.org/zones/chile-time.htm |archivedate=2007-09-11 }}</ref>\n| utc_offset = -4\n| timezone_DST = [[Time in Chile|CLST]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.world-time-zones.org/zones/chile-summer-time.htm |accessdate=2010-07-29 |title=Chile Summer Time |publisher=WorldTimeZones.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070911130451/http://www.world-time-zones.org/zones/chile-summer-time.htm |archivedate=2007-09-11 }}</ref>\n| utc_offset_DST = -3\n|postal_code_type       =  \n|postal_code            =\n|area_code              = ''country'' 56 + ''city'' 45\n|website                = {{URL|http://www.melipeuco.cl}}\n|footnotes              = \n}} \n'''Melipeuco''' ({{IPA-es|meli\u02c8peuko}}) is a [[List of towns in Chile|town]] and [[Communes of Chile|commune]] ({{lang-es|comuna}}) in [[Chile]], located at the foot of the [[Andes]], in the [[Caut\u00edn Province|Province of Caut\u00edn]], [[Araucan\u00eda Region]]. Melipeuco is {{convert|12|km|0|abbr=on}} from the southern entrance of the [[Conguill\u00edo National Park]]. The [[Nevados de Sollipulli]], an ice-filled volcanic [[caldera]] surrounded by numerous hot water springs and geysers, lie south of the town. Lake Carilafqu\u00e9n is also located in this area. At the edge of the Nevados de Sollipulli, at the Alpehue intersection {{convert|33|km|0|abbr=on}} away, there are several hot springs with water from {{convert|40|to|70|C|F}}, even in the middle of glacier blocks.\n\n==Demographics==\nAccording to the 2002 [[census]] of the [[National Statistics Institute (Chile)|National Statistics Institute]], Melipeuco spans an area of {{convert|1107.3|sqkm|0|abbr=on}} and has 5,628 inhabitants (2,906 men and 2,722 women). Of these, 2,333 (41.5%) lived in [[urban area]]s and 3,295 (58.5%) in [[rural area]]s. The population grew by 5.9% (315 persons) between the 1992 and 2002 censuses.<ref name= \"INE\"/>\n\n==Administration==\nAs a commune, Melipeuco is a third-level [[administrative division of Chile]] administered by a [[municipal council]], headed by an [[alcalde]] who is directly elected every four years. The 2008-2012 alcalde is Eduardo Navarrete Fuentes ([[Independent Democratic Union|UDI]]).<ref name=\"Munitel\"/><ref name=\"Official\"/>\n\nWithin the [[electoral divisions of Chile]], Melipeuco is represented in the [[Chamber of Deputies of Chile|Chamber of Deputies]] by Enrique Estay (UDI) and Fuad Chah\u00edn ([[Christian Democratic Party|PDC]]) as part of the 49th electoral district, (together with [[Victoria, Chile|Victoria]], [[Curacaut\u00edn]], [[Lonquimay]], [[Vilc\u00fan]], [[Lautaro, Chile|Lautaro]], [[Perquenco]] and [[Galvarino, Chile|Galvarino]]). The commune is represented in the [[Senate of Chile|Senate]] by Alberto Espina Otero ([[National Renewal (Chile)|RN]]) and Jaime Quintana Leal ([[Party for Democracy (Chile)|PPD]]) as part of the 14th senatorial constituency (Araucan\u00eda-North).\n\n==View==\n[[File:Iss038e012569, Caldera Sollipulli.jpg|500px|left|thumb|<center>''Sollipulli''</center>]]\n{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{in lang|es}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20170915001335/http://melipeuco.cl/ Municipality of Melipeuco]\n\n{{Communes in Araucan\u00eda Region}}\n\n[[Category:Communes of Chile]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1981]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Caut\u00edn Province]]\n", "name_user": "Nardog", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:fixingSpanish IPAperdiscussion", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melipeuco"}
{"title_page": "Mitchel Brown", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Mitchel Brown\n| image          = \n| fullname       = Glen Mitchel Brown James\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1981|7|16|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[La Ceiba]], [[Honduras]] \n| height         = {{convert|1.83|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}} \n| currentclub    = \n| clubnumber     = \n| position       = [[Striker (football)|Striker]] \n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = [[Victoria Leyde]] \n| years1         = 2000 \n| years2         = 2001\n| years3         = 2002\u20132004\n| years4         = 2004\u20132005\n| years5         = 2005\u20132007\n| years6         = 2007\n| years7         = 2007\u20132008 \n| years8         = 2008 \n| years9         = 2009 \n| years10        = 2010\u20132011\n| years11        = 2012\n| years12        = 2013\u20132014\n| years13        = 2014\n| years14        = 2015\n| clubs1         = [[Tertona FC|Tertona ]] \n| clubs2         = [[Brescia Calcio|Brescia]] \n| clubs3         = [[C.D. Suchitep\u00e9quez|Suchitep\u00e9quez]] \n| clubs4         = [[F.C. Motagua|Motagua]] \n| clubs5         = [[C.D. Victoria|Victoria]]\n| clubs6         = [[C.D. Marath\u00f3n|Marath\u00f3n]] \n| clubs7         = [[1. FC Tatran Pre\u0161ov|Tatran Pre\u0161ov]] \n| clubs8         = [[Qingdao Jonoon]] \n| clubs9         = [[C.D. Marath\u00f3n|Marath\u00f3n]]\n| clubs10        = [[Hunan Billows]]\n| clubs11        = [[C.D. Marath\u00f3n|Marath\u00f3n]]\n| clubs12        = [[Hubei China-Kyle]]\n| clubs13        = [[C.D. Marath\u00f3n|Marath\u00f3n]]\n| clubs14        = [[C.D.S. Vida|Vida]]\n| caps1          = 15   \n| caps2          = \n| caps3          =  \n| caps4          = 7   \n| caps5          = 69\n| caps6          = 18  \n| caps7          = 20   \n| caps8          = 23   \n| caps9          = 34\n| caps10         = 39\n| caps11         = 34\n| caps12         = 15\n| caps13         = 12\n| caps14         = 6\n| goals1         = 7  \n| goals2         = \n| goals3         = 45  \n| goals4         = 1  \n| goals5         = 16\n| goals6         = 8  \n| goals7         = 7  \n| goals8         = 7  \n| goals9         = 13\n| goals10        = 20\n| goals11        = 8\n| goals12        = 6\n| goals13        = 1\n| goals14        = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2008\u20132013\n| nationalteam1  = [[Honduras national football team|Honduras]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 3\n| nationalgoals1 = 0 \n| pcupdate       = 30 October 2011\n| ntupdate       = February 6, 2008 \n}}\n\n{{spanish name 2|Brown|James}}\n'''Glen Mitchel Brown James''' ({{IPA-es|\u02c8mit\u0283el \u02c8\u03b2\u027eawn}};{{efn|In isolation, ''Brown'' is pronounced {{IPA-es|\u02c8b\u027eawn|}}.}} born 16 July 1981), nicknamed \"El Depredador\" (''The Predator''), is a [[Honduras|Honduran]] [[soccer]] player.\n\n==Club career==\nA much-travelled forward, Brown has played in Italy, Guatemala, Slovakia and China along with his native Honduras.\n\nHis first goal was against [[Universidad NAH|Universidad]] playing for [[F.C. Motagua]] and after scoring he was expelled for taking off his shirt. He joined [[Qingdao Jonoon]] in 2008. He scored his first goal on the club on April 9, 2008.\n\n===China===\nBrown signed a contract with [[Hunan Billows]] in February 2010.<ref>[http://sports.sohu.com/20100228/n270475740.shtml \u6e56\u5357\u6e58\u6d9b\u65e0\u7f18\u54e5\u4f26\u6bd4\u4e9a\u7403\u661f \u7b7e\u6d2a\u90fd\u62c9\u65af\u73b0\u5f79\u56fd\u811a] {{in lang|zh}}</ref> He made his [[China League One]] debut for Hunan against [[Shenyang Dongjin]] on 3 April. Brown scored his first goal for the club on his fourth appearance,in a 2\u20131 home win against [[Shanghai East Asia]] on 22 April.<ref>[http://sports.sina.com.cn/b/2010-04-22/17034951088.shtml \u738b\u4f73\u7389\u4efb\u610f\u7403\u5efa\u529f\u738b\u741b\u8865\u65f6\u7edd\u6740 \u6e56\u5357\u4e3b\u573a2-1\u4e1c\u4e9a]{{in lang|zh}}</ref> In the 2010 league season, Brown was the top scorer of the club. He scored 7 goals in 19 appearances and won a new contract of the club. In January 2011, Costa Rican club [[L.D. Alajuelense]] was reported to be interested in Brown<ref>[http://www.diez.hn/content/view/full/22036 El Alajuelense est\u00e1 interesado en Mitchel Brown] - Diez {{in lang|es}}</ref> but a deal never materialized.\n\nBrown finished the 2011 league season with the League One top scorer, scored 13 goals in 20 appearances, which shared with [[Johnny Woodly Lambert|Johnny Woodly]].\n\nIn August 2012, while playing for Marath\u00f3n, Brown was involved in an incident in which Motagua goalkeeper Kerpo de Le\u00f3n was critically injured<ref>[http://www.laprensa.hn/Secciones-Principales/Deportes/Liga-de-Honduras/Kerpo-de-Leon-Tuve-miedo-de-morir Kerpo de Le\u00f3n: \u201cTuve miedo de morir \u201d] - La Prensa {{in lang|es}}</ref> and a committee summoned an investigation.<ref>[http://www.laprensa.hn/Secciones-Principales/Deportes/Liga-de-Honduras/Comision-de-Disciplina-cita-a-Mitchel-Brown Comisi\u00f3n de Disciplina cita a Mitchel Brown] - La Prensa {{in lang|es}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nHe made his debut for the national side on February 6, 2008 in a friendly against [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]], coming on as a substitute for [[Carlos Costly]].\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Clubs===\n*'''[[Liga Nacional de F\u00fatbol de Honduras|Honduran League]]: 2'''\n:: 2007 Apertura, 2009 Apertura (Marath\u00f3n),\n\n* Runner-up with Victoria: 2006 Clausura\n* Runner-up with Suchitepequez:\n* Promotion with Suchitepequez\n\n===Individual===\n*[[China League One]] top scorer: [[2011 China League One|2011]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{NFT player|pid=25063}}\n\n{{China League One top scorers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Brown, Mitchel}}\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from La Ceiba]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Honduran footballers]]\n[[Category:Honduras international footballers]]