{"title_page": "In\u00e9s Sainz", "text_new": "{{short description|Mexican model and sports journalist}}\n{{Distinguish|In\u00e9s S\u00e1inz Esteban}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = In\u00e9s Sainz\n| image       = In\u00e9s_Sainz_Gallo.jpg\n| caption     = Sainz in 2013\n| birth_name  =\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1978|9|20}}<ref name = reporterclaiming>{{cite news|url = http://www.nydailynews.com/ny_local/2010/09/13/2010-09-13_ines_sainz_mexican_sports_reporter_claiming_sexual_harassment_by_jets_uses_twitt.html|newspaper = [[New York Daily News]]|date = September 13, 2010|title = Ines Sainz, reporter in Jets sexual harassment firestorm, defends self, denies feeling offended|first1 = Michael|last = Sheridan|first2 = Meena|last2 = Hartenstein}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Quer\u00e9taro, Quer\u00e9taro]], [[Mexico]]\n| residence   =[[Mexico City]],<ref name = \"world'shottest\"/> Mexico\n| other_names =\n| education   =\n| home_town   = [[Quer\u00e9taro, Quer\u00e9taro]], [[Mexico]]<ref name = nosoytan/>\n| spouse      = H\u00e9ctor P\u00e9rez Rojano<br>[[Television producer]]\n| children    =\n| parents     =\n| relatives   =\n| television  = [[TV Azteca]]&thinsp;/&thinsp;[[Azteca America]]'s<br>''Deportips Y Mas''<br>''Los Protagonistas''<br>''De Safari''\n| known_for   =\n| nationality = [[Mexico|Mexican]]\n| occupation  =  Television personality, sports reporter, model\n| height      = {{height|ft=5|in=7}}\n| weight      =\n| years_active= 2001\u2013present\n| module      =\n| website     = {{url|inessainz.mx}}\n}}\n{{spanish name 2|Sainz|Gallo}}\n'''In\u00e9s Sainz Gallo de P\u00e9rez''' ({{IPA-es|i\u02c8nes \u02c8sajns}}; September 20, 1978)<ref name = reporterclaiming/> is a [[Mexico|Mexican]] journalist hosting the Spanish-language sports interview program ''DxTips'' (or, ''Deportips''); she is also a journalist for [[Azteca Deportes]]. Sainz and her husband,  who reside in Mexico, own the production company that created the show.<ref name = debeines/>  Sainz works in the English language as a boxing match hostess.\n\n== Biography ==\nSainz grew up in a family with three siblings in [[Mexico City, Mexico]], all of them brothers, one her twin. Although Sainz was an athletic tomboy active in a number of sports (she became a [[black belt (martial arts)|black belt]] in [[taekwondo]] at the age of 14, competing in national competitions) Sainz's mother, a homemaker, wanted her to be more feminine, and encouraged her to enter professional modeling,<ref name = \"world'shottest\"/> which she did, shooting commercials for such companies as [[Bacardi]], [[List of companies of Mexico#H|''Hoteles Misi\u00f3n'']], and [[Telcel]].<ref name=solohablaconestrellas>{{cite news|newspaper = [[El Universal (Mexico City)|El Universal]]|first = Maru|last = Ruiz de Icaza|date = June 29, 2004|title = In\u00e9s S\u00e1inz s\u00f3lo habla con estrellas|url = http://www2.eluniversal.com.mx/pls/impreso/noticia.html?id_nota=35415&tabla=nuestromundo|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20100912060543/http://www2.eluniversal.com.mx/pls/impreso/noticia.html?id_nota=35415&tabla=nuestromundo|archivedate = September 12, 2010}}</ref>\n\nSainz graduated with a [[Licentiate (degree)|''licenciatura en derecho'' (\"bachelor in law\")]] degree from the [[Universidad del Valle de Mexico]] in Quer\u00e9taro and a masters in [[tax law]] from the [[Universidad Aut\u00f3noma de Quer\u00e9taro]].<ref name = laperiodistamexicana/> Her father was likewise a lawyer. Additionally, Sainz obtained a graduate degree in sports [[business administration]].<ref name = sainztocover/> Moving from modeling to television sports reporting,<ref name = \"world'shottest\"/> Sainz married Mexican television producer H\u00e9ctor P\u00e9rez Rojano and they have four children, Mar\u00eda In\u00e9s, Eduardo,  Hector, and Maya.<ref name = nosoytan>{{cite news|publisher=La Prensa Honduras|date=April 3, 2009|first=Sabino|last=G\u00e1mez|title=In\u00e9s Sainz: 'No soy tan vanidosa'|trans-title=In\u00e9s Sainz: 'I'm not that vain'|url=http://www.laprensa.hn/Deportes/Ediciones/2009/04/04/Noticias/Ines-Sainz-No-soy-tan-vanidosa|language=Spanish|quote=Est\u00e1 casada con H\u00e9ctor P\u00e9rez Rojado y tiene tres hijos: una ni\u00f1a llamada Mar\u00eda In\u00e9s de cinco a\u00f1os y dos gemelos que nacieron en octubre del a\u00f1o pasado y que los bautiz\u00f3 como H\u00e9ctor y Eduardo P\u00e9rez Sainz. ... Su trabajo no s\u00f3lo se resume en trabajar como conductora con apariciones diarias, sino hacer la producci\u00f3n independiente de Deportips en su propia productora. ... ...El encanto de esta chica nacida en Ciudad de M\u00e9xico, pero criada en Quer\u00e9taro.... (\"She is married to Hector Perez Rojado and has three children: a daughter named Maria Ines of five years and twins born in October last year named Hector and Eduardo Perez Sainz. ... The work entails not only duties as host of Deportips with daily appearances but also as an executive of its independent production. ... ...The charm of this girl native of Mexico City but raised in Queretaro....\")}}</ref><ref name=debeines>{{cite news|url = http://www.elmanana.com.mx/notas.asp?id=103783|title = Debe In\u00e9s Sainz su figura al deporte Mi\u00e9rcoles|date = February 11, 2009|first = Brenda|last = Molina|agency = Agencia Reforma|newspaper = [[El Ma\u00f1ana (Nuevo Laredo)|El Ma\u00f1ana]]|location = [[Nuevo Laredo, Tamaulipas]]|quote = En octubre, la reportera dio a luz a H\u00e9ctor y Eduardo, productos de su segundo embarazo. ... In\u00e9s Sainz se dio a conocer gracias al programa \"Deportips\", el cual se transmiti\u00f3 por primera vez el 20 de septiembre de 2002 y que sigue al aire. Su esposo, H\u00e9ctor P\u00e9rez Rojano, y ella son los productores de dicha emisi\u00f3n. (\"In October, the journalist gave birth to Hector and Eduardo, products of her second pregnancy. ... Ines Sainz debuted thanks to the program Deportips, which first aired on September 20, 2002 and continues to air. Her husband, Hector Perez Rojano, and she are the producers of every episode.\")|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110722224050/http://www.elmanana.com.mx/notas.asp?id=103783|archivedate = July 22, 2011}}</ref><ref name = femalesportsreporter/> Sainz remained an active participant herself in such sports as [[association football|football]], swimming, volleyball, basketball and tennis.<ref name = solohablaconestrellas/><ref name = laperiodistamexicana>{{cite news|date = June 7, 2006|title = In\u00e9s Sainz la periodista mexicana que levant\u00f3 a toda Argentina|url = http://www.sitiosargentina.com.ar/notas/2006/junio/ines-sainz.htm|publisher = Sitios Argentinas Notas & Noticias|quote = Seg\u00fan informa la TV Azteca en su p\u00e1gina de internet, In\u00e9s es 'egresada de la carrera de Leyes por la Universidad del Valle de M\u00e9xico en Quer\u00e9taro, y con una maestr\u00eda en Derecho Fiscal por la Universidad Aut\u00f3noma de Quer\u00e9taro'. Adem\u00e1s da cuenta de que \u201cha entrevistado a algunos de los deportistas m\u00e1s destacados del orbe como Ronaldo, Roberto Carlos, Rivaldo, Zinedine Zidane y Shaquille O`Nelly\u201d. Adem\u00e1s de haber jugado al f\u00fatbol de sal\u00f3n, tambi\u00e9n practic\u00f3 nataci\u00f3n, voley, basquet y tenis. Pero eso no es todo, ya que la actual conductora de 'Deportips' adem\u00e1s es cintur\u00f3n negro de tae-kwan-do. (\"As reported by TV Azteca on its website, Ines was 'a graduate in law from the Universidad del Valle de Mexico in Queretaro and a masters in tax law from the Autonomous University of Quer\u00e9taro.' Also it's realized that 'she has interviewed some of the world's leading athletes such as Ronaldo, Roberto Carlos, Rivaldo, Zinedine Zidane and Shaquille O'Neal.' Besides having played indoor association football and practiced swimming, volleyball, basketball and tennis. But that's not all, because the current host of Deportips is also a black belt in taekwando.\")}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== Public image ===\nIn 2010, TV Azteca's website's featured photo galleries of her as well as an article in its \"Bad Girls\" section extolling her as a woman of intelligence and humor, illustrated by a photo of her modeling a swimsuit.<ref>{{cite news|publisher = Associated Press|url = https://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5jxB1UjbIt4BBBxEeyWKK7kW33JLAD9I7AM7O0|title = NFL talks to female reporter about Jets behavior|first = Dennis|last = Waszak Jr.|date = September 14, 2010}}</ref> Likewise, during the 2000s, Sainz appeared on the cover of  such Spanish-language magazines as ''Revista Gente y la Actualidad,''<ref>{{cite news|work = Philly.com|url = http://www.philly.com/philly/entertainment/102934814.html?imageId=40281719|title = Inez Sainz on the cover of Gente magazine|accessdate = September 18, 2010}}</ref> ''[[H Para Hombres]],'' [[Maxim (magazine)#Expansion of the Maxim brand|''Maxim'']], and [[Esquire (magazine)|''Esquire Mexico'']].<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.myfoxboston.com/dpps/sports/ines-sainz-mexican-sports-reporter-ny-jets-dpgoha-20100914-fc_9626116|work = MyFoxBoston|date = September 14, 2010|title = Who is Ines Sainz?|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120212130622/http://www.myfoxboston.com/dpps/sports/ines-sainz-mexican-sports-reporter-ny-jets-dpgoha-20100914-fc_9626116|archivedate = February 12, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://guyism.com/2010/05/super-hot-sideline-reporter-ines-sainz-bikinis-it-up-in-esquire-mexico.html|website=Guyism|title=Super hot sideline reporter Ines Sainz bikinis it up in Esquire Mexico|first=DC|last=Scrap|accessdate=September 17, 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100918203751/http://guyism.com/2010/05/super-hot-sideline-reporter-ines-sainz-bikinis-it-up-in-esquire-mexico.html|archivedate=September 18, 2010}}</ref> Prior and during the 2010 World Cup, pictures of Sainz were featured on such places as ''[[Bleacher Report]]''<ref>{{cite web|website = [[Bleacher Report]]|url = http://bleacherreport.com/articles/395867-sexy-world-cup-mexico#page/18|date = May 23, 2010|title = World Cup WAGs: Team Mexico|first = Andrew|last = Kearney}}</ref> and the websites run by ''[[Sports Illustrated]]''<ref>{{cite magazine|magazine = [[Sports Illustrated]]|first = Jimmy|last = Traina|url = http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2010/extramustard/hotclicks/06/16/ines-sainz-terrell-owens-incredible-high-jump/index.html|title = T.O.'s up|date = June 16, 2010}}</ref> and ''[[Men's Health (magazine)|Men's Health]].''<ref name=\"world'shottest\">{{cite web|url = http://www.menshealth.com/women-of-mh/models/ines-sainz?page=1#modelpic|title = Is Ines Sainz the World's Hottest Woman?|publisher = [[Men's Health (magazine)|Men's Health]]|work = Women of MH|date = September 17, 2010|access-date = 2010-09-23|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100918093434/http://www.menshealth.com/women-of-mh/models/ines-sainz?page=1#modelpic#modelpic|archive-date = 2010-09-18|url-status = dead}}</ref>  Sainz was chosen by the magazine ''[[FHM]]'' as the fifth sexiest woman sports reporter in the world in August 2009.<ref>{{cite web|work=[[FHM]] Online |url=http://www.fhmonline.com/site/content/article.aspx?id=41540 |title=The Five Sexiest Sports Reporters in the World |date=August 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100811051107/http://www.fhmonline.com/site/content/article.aspx?id=41540 |archivedate=2010-08-11 }}</ref>\n\n=== Sports reporting ===\n[[File:Ines Sainz.jpg|thumb|right|In\u00e9s Sainz at the Mexico vs. North Korea [[international friendly]] [[association football|football]] match in [[Torre\u00f3n, Coahuila]], Mexico, on March 17, 2010.]]\n\nSainz has interviewed, among others, [[tennis]] players [[Roger Federer]] and [[Rafael Nadal]], [[basketball]] players [[Kobe Bryant]] and [[Shaquille O'Neal]], [[baseball]] players [[Derek Jeter]] and [[Alex Rodriguez]] and [[association football]] players [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]], [[Roberto Carlos (footballer)|Roberto Carlos]], [[Rivaldo]], [[Zinedine Zidane]], [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] and [[Lionel Messi]].<ref name = laperiodistamexicana/><ref name = femalesportsreporter/><ref>{{Cite news|publisher = [[NBC Sports]]|url = http://outofbounds.nbcsports.com/2010/09/castrodale-8.html.php|title = Castrodale: Ines Sainz shouldn't have to explain herself; it's the men who are acting like idiots|date = September 16, 2010|first = Jelisa|last = Castrodale|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20100918035522/http://outofbounds.nbcsports.com/2010/09/castrodale-8.html.php|archivedate = September 18, 2010}}</ref> By July 2006, Sainz had covered three [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] tournaments and four [[NBA Finals]], the [[2004 Athens Olympics]] and the [[2006 World Cup]].<ref name = bella>{{cite news|title = A In\u00e9s, ser bella le da privilegios|date = July 11, 2006|newspaper = [[El Universal (Mexico City)|El Universal]]|url = http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/estilos/49298.html}}</ref> As of 2009, Sainz had covered six Super Bowls,<ref>{{cite news|newspaper = [[San Francisco Examiner]]|agency = Associated Press|url = http://www.sfexaminer.com/sports/Super_Bowl_media_day_a_true_circus.html|title = Super Bowl media day a true circus|date = January 28, 2009|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110616142120/http://www.sfexaminer.com/sports/Super_Bowl_media_day_a_true_circus.html|archivedate = June 16, 2011}}</ref> the first, [[Super Bowl XXXVI]] in 2002.<ref name = 60seconds>{{cite news|url = http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_8163/is_20070131/ai_n51949013/|date = January 31, 2007|newspaper = [[Palm Beach Post]]|title = 60 Seconds with Ines Sainz|first = Tom|last = D'Angelo}}</ref> In January 2009, promoting American football stars to a Mexican audience, Sainz ran an informal biceps competition during the [[Super Bowl XLIII]] \"media day,\" awarding her \"Strongest Right Arm\" award to the [[Arizona Cardinals]]' [[defensive end]] [[Antonio Smith (defensive end)|Antonio Smith]].<ref>{{Cite news|work = AZCentral.com|url = http://www.azcentral.com/sports/cardinals/articles/2009/01/27/20090127spt-sbbickley.html|date = January 27, 2009|title = Bickley: Cards handle media-day blitz well|first = Dan|last = Bickley}}</ref> According to the ''[[Palm Beach Post]],'' at the 2007 Super Bowl's \"media day,\" Sainz was photographed as often as [[Peyton Manning]];<ref name = 60seconds/> and according to ''[[The Daily Telegraph]],'' she was \"besides Manning, the single-most popular person on the premises.\"<ref>{{cite news|newspaper = The Daily Telegraph|title = Colts and Bears fed to hungry 4,000|first = Art|last = Spander|date = February 1, 2007|url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/othersports/2307056/Colts-and-Bears-fed-to-hungry-4000.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|magazine = [[Newsweek]]|url = http://www.newsweek.com/2007/01/30/media-day.html|title = Media Day|date = January 30, 2007}}</ref> During a period when [[Terrell Owens]] was not speaking with the press in 2008, it was only Sainz who was able to gain an exclusive interview with the wide receiver.<ref name = reporterclaiming/>\n\nBoxing promotion company [[Top Rank]] hired Sainz to conduct pre-event reports and interviews and offer ringside commentary for the [[Manny Pacquiao vs. Antonio Margarito]] World [[Super Welterweight]] Championship bout in [[Arlington, Texas]] on November 13, 2010.<ref name = sainztocover>{{cite web|url = http://www.proboxing-fans.com/super-sexy-ines-sainz-to-cover-pacquiao-vs-maragarito_101410/|date = October 14, 2010|title = Super Sexy Ines Sainz to Cover Pacquiao vs. Maragarito|work = ProBoxing-Fans.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|newspaper = [[USA Today]]|url = http://content.usatoday.com/communities/gameon/post/2010/10/ines-sainz-manny-pacquiao-fight/1|title = Ines Sainz will be a factor at Manny Pacquiao fight|date = October 14, 2010}}</ref> Sainz co-hosted broadcast commentary for the March 12, 2011 [[Miguel Cotto vs. Ricardo Mayorga]] bout.<ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.nowboxing.com/2011/03/watch-the-cotto-mayorga-weigh-in-live-online/16788/|publisher = NowBoxing.com|title = Watch the Cotto-Mayorga Weigh-in Live Online|date = March 11, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, it was announced that Sainz would be a host on the [[Netflix]] [[reality show]] ''[[Ultimate Beastmaster]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/digital/news/ultimate-beastmaster-netflix-competition-series-sylvester-stallone-dave-broome-1201769095/|title=Netflix Orders Global Competition Series \u2018Ultimate Beastmaster\u2019 from Sylvester Stallone, Dave Broome|last=Prudon|first=Laura|work=Variety|date=May 9, 2016|accessdate=October 5, 2016}}</ref> Sainz returned as a host for Mexicos second appearance in season 3.\n\n=== Controversy ===\nIn 2010 the TV Azteca reporter sought an interview with then [[NY Jets]] quarterback [[Mark Sanchez]], and she had been standing on the sidelines during practice when Jets players and coaches appeared to throw footballs in her direction. Later, as she waited in the locker room to conduct an interview with Sanchez, she was reportedly the target of lewd comments from players and staff. She tweeted in Spanish: \"I'm so uncomfortable! I'm in the Jets locker room waiting for Mark Sanchez and trying not to look around me.\" And a few moments later, she wrote, \"I want to cover my ears.\" Media persons reported that team members made \"catcalls and rude comments\".<ref name = othersbalked>{{cite news|url = http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2010/09/14/earlyshow/main6864708.shtml|date = September 14, 2010|title = Sainz: Others Balked at Jets' Behavior, Not Me: Says Colleagues Objected, Concluded It Was Wrong; Says She's Been Hassled Before -- Just Never So Rudely|publisher = [[CBS News]]}}</ref> According to Sainz, it was \"the rest of the media start to hear the different kind of things that I didn't hear.\"<ref name = othersbalked/> She accepted a personal apology from Jets owner [[Woody Johnson]] when those incidents became known to him.\n\nIn the immediate aftermath of the incident, Sainz lost a contract to be the spokesperson for a Mexican bank, which she said was \"very painful\" for her;<ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.startribune.com/sports/blogs/107517633.html?elr=KArksi8cyaiUo8cyaiUiD3aPc:_Yyc:aUGE:h4E77U|newspaper = [[Minneapolis Star Tribune]]|title = RandBall Q&A: Reporter Ines Sainz on the Mark Sanchez incident, T.O. and more|first = Michael|last = Rand|date = November 12, 2010}}</ref> however, she said that the publicity resulting from the event also led her to become \"the most popular journalist right now in Mexico and Latin America.\"<ref name = femalesportsreporter>{{cite news|publisher = McClatchy Newspapers|url = http://www.kansascity.com/2010/09/21/2241244/female-sports-reporter-from-mexico.html#ixzz10D2iqv2n|first = Tim|last = Johnson|title = Female sports reporter from Mexico surprised she's focus of much controversy|newspaper = [[Kansas City Star]]}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[In\u00e9s G\u00f3mez Mont]]\n* [[Mar\u00eda In\u00e9s|Mar\u00eda In\u00e9s Guerra]]\n* [[Association for Women in Sports Media]]\n* [[Lisa Olson]]\n* [[Jenn Sterger]]\n* [[Katherine Webb]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|In\u00e9s Sainz}}\n* {{official website|http://inessainz.mx}} {{in lang|es}}\n* [http://www.aztecaamerica.com/notas/antesaladeportiva/21434/jets-vs-sainz:-la-polemica-en-los-medios \"Notas Jets VS Sainz: la pol\u00e9mica en los medios\"] &ndash; AztecaAmerica.com\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100918040027/http://www.tvazteca.com/nota/laacademia/ines-sainz-en-la-academia/2009-10-348 Bio at TV Azteca]\n* [http://www.sportsgrid.com/nfl/ines-sainz-shares-her-story-with-cnns-rick-sanchez/ Ines Sainz Shares Her Story With CNN\u2019s Rick Sanchez (Video)] &ndash; ''Sports Grid'